annotationA: Defective proventriculus (Dve) is a transcriptional repressor that binds to the K50 site. Dve roles include developmental patterning, cell-type specification, and functional differentiation
annotationB: Death executioner caspase related to Apopain/Yama is one of the seven members of the caspase family of cysteine proteases. It has substrate specificity similar to the effector caspases Drice and Cp1; Belongs to the peptidase C14A family
